      • getAllReadableTokens

        public List<NamedToken> getAllReadableTokens​(PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
        Same as getTokens(PageCursorTracer), except tokens that cannot be read due to inconsistencies will just be ignored, while getTokens(PageCursorTracer) would throw an exception in such cases.
        Returns:
        All tokens that could be read without any apparent problems.

      • updateRecord

        public void updateRecord​(RECORD record,
                         IdUpdateListener idUpdateListener,
                         PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
        Description copied from interface: RecordStore
        Updates this store with the contents of record at the record id specified by the record. The whole record will be written if the given record is in use, not necessarily so if it's not in use.
        Specified by:
        updateRecord in interface RecordStore<RECORD extends TokenRecord>
        Overrides:

        Parameters:

        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer.

      • ensureHeavy

        public void ensureHeavy​(RECORD record,
                        PageCursorTracer cursorTracer)
        Description copied from interface: RecordStore
        For stores that have other stores coupled underneath, the "top level" record will have a flag saying whether or not it's light. Light means that no records from the coupled store have been loaded yet. This method can load those records and enrich the target record with those, marking it as heavy.
        Specified by:
        ensureHeavy in interface RecordStore<RECORD extends TokenRecord>
        Overrides:
        ensureHeavy in class CommonAbstractStore<RECORD extends TokenRecord,​NoStoreHeader>
        Parameters:
        record - record to make heavy, if not already.
        cursorTracer - underlying page cursor tracer.
